file_content.text: We may fall, but fear remains eternal!
My purpose has been served.
I am a small sacrifice.
Hounds of the Empire. How blindly you stumble without someone to hold your leash.
How they scuttle about, these defenders of "freedom," blindly denying the one true path before them.
Your Emperor is dead, but you may still serve a higher power. Kneel, and the masters will grant you purpose.
They deny the truth.
They fancy themselves important and their lives meaningful.
Abandon your free will, and avoid the agony of having it broken.
Those who will not serve will die!
We are the chosen!
You could have been one of us.
You will welcome death before the end.
We are more forgiving than the masters.
Your struggle only prolongs the pain.
You are many, but we are one!
The masters guide us while you remain blind!
The masters command, the Force obeys!
You will all share this fate!
Your destiny is fulfilled.
Consumed by fear.
The masters foresaw your demise.
None can stand before us.
The shield is broken, but the sword is now drawn.
